<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 26, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Closed the remaining promise/product gap on <a href="/goats" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/goats</a> by qualifying Linear Appraisal, FAMACHA, FEC, and FECRT references so they no longer read as fully-shipped audit-grade records, and neutralized dog-coded alt text on <a href="/for-breeders" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-breeders</a> screenshots so the page reads correctly for all nine supported species.</p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">/goats — claim cleanup</h3>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>Dairy production FAQ no longer lists "linear appraisal scores" alongside shipped DHIA fields; Linear Appraisal capture and DHIA bulk import are now described as 2026 roadmap items.</li>
    <li>Parasite-management FAQ (appears twice on the page, accordion + bottom FAQ) reworded from "Yes" to "In part, today" — FAMACHA and FEC remain available as storefront credibility chips, but structured FAMACHA / FEC / FECRT records are described as 2026 roadmap items.</li>
    <li>Hero subhead and meta description now say "FAMACHA/FEC credibility chips" rather than implying audit-grade records, and the hero subhead names the roadmap explicitly.</li>
