    <li>Offspring list screenshot alt text changed from "Litter view with collar colors" to "Offspring view with identifiers."</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Why this matters</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">The goat audit identified that marketing copy was promising FAMACHA, FEC, FECRT, and Linear Appraisal as if they were fully-shipped audit-grade record types. They are not yet — what ships today is storefront credibility chips plus per-animal/group deworming and medication records. Leaving the bald claims in place is a credibility detonation the moment a serious ADGA or ABGA operator logs in. The same audit flagged that the highest-traffic shared breeder landing page tagged its hero image as a "Labrador breeder," undermining the multi-species message immediately. Both are pure copy/alt-text changes — no URL changes, no navigation changes, no schema changes.</p>
